body:
This question from [issues/232#issuecomment-528840847](https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/issues/232#issuecomment-528840847)
``` cs
// get the character code
// either:
var emojiChar = StringUtilities.GetUnicodeCharacterCode("🚀", SKTextEncoding.Utf32);
// or:
var emojiChar = 0x1F680;

// ask the font manager for a font with that character
var fontManager = SKFontManager.Default;
var emojiTypeface = fontManager.MatchCharacter(emojiChar);

// draw it
var paint = new SKPaint { Typeface = emoji };
canvas.DrawText("🌐 🍪 🍕 🚀", 20, 40, paint);
```
